52. Such alliterations as sce- lesta sola secum are very fre- quently found in the ancient Roman poets and merit our especial attention. We shall here point out only a few ex- amples which occur in the next lines: dedam discipulam 59. metuo male 61. miserum modis 66. miseram modum 69. decies die 70.
